    "field": "finance",
    "role": "instrument",
    "bullets": [
      "Firm-level panel of listed firms; the sample period and country are not stated in the abstract, and the unit of observation is the firm.",
      "FinBERT2, a finance-domain BERT model, constructs a firm-level physical climate risk indicator from text; no validation against hand-coded labels is reported.",
      "Higher physical climate risk raises trade credit occupation, especially from upstream suppliers, and propagates supply chain contagion that lowers supplier performance and resilience, while supplier concentration curbs the effect."
    ],
